\alpha = x dy-\frac{1}{2}(x^2+y^2)dt
\mathbb{R}^3=\{(x,y,t)\}
 \begin{align*} d\alpha &= dx\wedge dy - \frac{1}{2}(2x dx+2y dy)dt \\&= dx\wedge dy- x dx\wedge dt- y dy\wedge dt \end{align*}
 dt\wedge d\alpha = dt\wedge dx\wedge dy = dx\wedge dy\wedge dt \qquad \text{by anticommutativity} 
 dx\wedge d\alpha = -y dx\wedge dy\wedge dt 
